<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="421" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,497,1338,1402]" box="[151,408,1374,1402]" pageId="6" pageNumber="421">
(
<figureCitation box="[160,237,1375,1401]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1772,1796]" captionTargetBox="[158,1427,355,1737]" captionTargetId="figure-91@5.[149,1438,345,1749]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4. a. Beanoides nitida male Thailand, Lampang, Chae Hom 12.ix.2015 b. male Thailand, Lampang, Muban Phichai 28.vii.2012 c. female Thailand, Lampang, Muban Phichai 10.iii.2014 d. Beana terminigera male Thailand, Chiangmai, Pa Pae 12.vii.2012 e. female Thailand, Lampang, Muban Phichai 23.vi.2017 f. female Thailand, Lampang, Muban Phichai 27.vii.2008" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4595447" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4595447/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="421">Fig.s 4</figureCitation>
a–c and 5 a–d)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,555,1443,1468]" box="[151,555,1443,1468]" pageId="6" pageNumber="421">
<typeStatus box="[151,201,1444,1468]" pageId="6" pageNumber="421">Type</typeStatus>
species: 
<taxonomicName authority="Tams, 1924" authorityName="Tams" authorityYear="1924" box="[294,552,1443,1467]" class="Insecta" family="Nolidae" genus="Beana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="421" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nitida">
<emphasis box="[294,424,1443,1467]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="421">Beana nitida</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Tams, W. H. T." box="[430,552,1443,1467]" pageId="6" pageNumber="421" pagination="229 - 289" refId="ref3733" refString="Tams, W. H. T. (1924) List of the moth, collected in Siam by E. J. Godfrey B. SC., F. E. S. Journal of theNatural History Society of Siam, 6, 229 - 289." type="journal article" year="1924">Tams, 1924</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,1513,1828]" pageId="6" pageNumber="421">
Currently 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pellinen &amp; Wahlberg" authorityYear="2021" box="[266,383,1513,1539]" class="Insecta" family="Nolidae" genus="Beanoides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="421" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[266,383,1513,1539]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="421">Beanoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a monotypic genus, including 
<taxonomicName box="[754,850,1513,1539]" class="Insecta" family="Nolidae" genus="Beana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="421" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nitida">
<emphasis box="[754,850,1513,1539]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="421">B. nitida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
only. It belongs to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stainton" authorityYear="1859" box="[1067,1235,1513,1539]" class="Insecta" family="Nolidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="421" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Chloephorinae">Chloephorinae</taxonomicName>
, best placed close to genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Walker 1864" authorityName="Walker" authorityYear="1864" box="[255,502,1549,1575]" class="Insecta" family="Nolidae" genus="Ariolica" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="421" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[255,347,1549,1575]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="421">Ariolica</emphasis>
Walker 1864
</taxonomicName>
. Externally 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pellinen &amp; Wahlberg" authorityYear="2021" box="[640,757,1549,1575]" class="Insecta" family="Nolidae" genus="Beanoides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="421" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[640,757,1549,1575]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="421">Beanoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is different from 
<taxonomicName box="[958,1067,1549,1575]" class="Insecta" family="Nolidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="421" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Ariolicini">Ariolicini</taxonomicName>
species, but male genitalia have similarities; apical form of valva, exterior basal hair-pencil (not strong in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pellinen &amp; Wahlberg" authorityYear="2021" box="[960,1077,1585,1611]" class="Insecta" family="Nolidae" genus="Beanoides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="421" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[960,1077,1585,1611]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="421">Beanoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) in valves, aedeagus vesica with several small spines also tymbal organ is not present in the basal sternal sclerite, though there are other features that connect 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pellinen &amp; Wahlberg" authorityYear="2021" box="[246,363,1657,1683]" class="Insecta" family="Nolidae" genus="Beanoides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="421" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[246,363,1657,1683]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="421">Beanoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Walker" authorityYear="1864" box="[399,491,1657,1683]" class="Insecta" family="Nolidae" genus="Ariolica" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="421" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[399,491,1657,1683]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="421">Ariolica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
like the narrow basal sternal sclerite with somewhat longer and narrower apodemes on either side of a generally concave margin.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="421" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,1513,1828]" pageId="6" pageNumber="421">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,518,1729,1755]" pageId="6" pageNumber="421">Diagnosis and Description.</emphasis>
The new genus resembles 
<taxonomicName box="[816,1026,1730,1755]" class="Insecta" family="Nolidae" genus="Beana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="421" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="terminigera">
<emphasis box="[816,1026,1730,1755]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="421">Beana terminigera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[1041,1117,1729,1755]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1772,1796]" captionTargetBox="[158,1427,355,1737]" captionTargetId="figure-91@5.[149,1438,345,1749]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4. a. Beanoides nitida male Thailand, Lampang, Chae Hom 12.ix.2015 b. male Thailand, Lampang, Muban Phichai 28.vii.2012 c. female Thailand, Lampang, Muban Phichai 10.iii.2014 d. Beana terminigera male Thailand, Chiangmai, Pa Pae 12.vii.2012 e. female Thailand, Lampang, Muban Phichai 23.vi.2017 f. female Thailand, Lampang, Muban Phichai 27.vii.2008" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4595447" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4595447/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="421">Fig.s 4</figureCitation>
d–f and 5 e–h) externally by size (wingspan ~ 
<quantity box="[342,469,1765,1792]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.45" metricValueMax="3.5" metricValueMin="3.4" pageId="6" pageNumber="421" unit="mm" value="34.5" valueMax="35.0" valueMin="34.0">34–35 mm</quantity>
), although it is more variable in the forewing pattern. There is no clear sexual dimorphism in 
<taxonomicName box="[255,444,1801,1827]" class="Insecta" family="Nolidae" genus="Beanoides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="421" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nitida">
<emphasis box="[255,444,1801,1827]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="421">Beanoides nitida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
